Diagram 2 (Ineffective)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par What if black hanes at 1?
\par This lacks effectiveness. White plays dansu at 2 and there is no move left.
\par
\par Even if black connects at 3, white plays dansu at 4 and lives.
\par
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj However, it is worth mentioning that it is now seonsu for black to descent at 5. If white doesn't play at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , black plays at \b\f1 B\b0\f0  killing white.
\par \pard
\par }
