Diagram 3 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Black's diagonal move is a vital point that is not easy to find unless you know of it. It aims at capturing the three white \'a1\'e2 stones.
\par
\par Actually, it is not just the three white stones but white's whole group.
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj Now even if white connects at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , the group is dead.
\par }
